    <preface>
      <p class="center"><docType><b>EXPLANATORY MEMORANDUM TO </b></docType></p>
      <p class="center"><b>THE FINANCIAL SERVICES AND MARKETS ACT 2000 (REGULATED ACTIVITIES) (AMENDMENT) (NO.2) ORDER 2013 </b></p>
      <p class="center"><docNumber><b>No. </b></docNumber></p>
      <p class="center"><b>AND </b></p>
      <p class="center"><b>THE FINANCIAL SERVICES ACT 2012 (CONSUMER CREDIT) ORDER 2013</b></p>
      <p class="center"><docNumber><b>No. </b></docNumber></p>
    </preface>
    <mainBody>
      <toc>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukdsi/2013/9780111100493/memorandum/1" level="1"><inline name="tocHeading">The whole Explanatory Memorandum</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukdsi/2013/9780111100493/memorandum/1/paragraph/1" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">1. This explanatory memorandum has been prepared by HM Treasury and is laid before Parliament by...</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukdsi/2013/9780111100493/memorandum/1/paragraph/2" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">2. Purpose of the instrument</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukdsi/2013/9780111100493/memorandum/1/paragraph/3" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">3. Matters of special interest to the Joint Committee on Statutory Instruments</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukdsi/2013/9780111100493/memorandum/1/paragraph/4" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">4. Legislative Context</inline></tocItem>
